$ Web platform

The → https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_platform[Web platform] includes 
  • → development/web/HTML
  • → development/web/CSS
  • → design/graphic/svg
  • MathML
  • WAI-ARIA (the *Accessible Rich Internet Applications Suite* of the *Web Accessibility Initiative*)
  • ECMAScript (See → development/languages/JavaScript)
  • → development/web/WebGL
  • Web Storage
  • Indexed Database API
  • Web Components
  • → development/web/browser/WebAssembly
  • → development/web/platform/WebGPU
  • Web Workers
  • WebSocket (How does this relate to XMLHttpRequest?)
  • Geolocation API
  • Server-Sent Events
  • DOM Events
  • Media Fragments
  • XMLHttpRequest (How does this relate to WebSocket?)
  • Cross-Origin Resource Sharing
  • File API
  • RDFa
  • WOFF
  • → development/web/HTTP
  • → development/security/cryptography/SSL-TLS[TLS] 1.2
  • → development/web/URI-URL-URN-IRI-URC#iri[IRI]

These technologies are developed as *open standards* by the
   • World Wide Web Consortium
   • Web Hypertext Application Technology Working Group
   • Unicode Consortium
   • Internet Engineering Task Force
   • Ecma International
  

